">WordPress repo</a>. <del\ndatetime="2014-11-04T00:51:58+00:00"><em>OR</em><em> <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/wordpress-custom-login-pro/" title="WordPress Custom Login Pro">Custom Login Pro</a>.</em></del> <ins\ndatetime="2014-11-04T00:51:58+00:00">As of version 1.1.0 this plugin does not work with CLP.</ins></strong></p><p\nclass="note"><strong>New:</strong> In Custom Login as of version 2.2 you can now auto-install this extension from within your WordPress website! Just visit the Custom Login settings page and click &#8220;install&#8221; and enter your license key when prompted! No need to download the zip and upload the files.</p><h2>WordPress Login Redirects</h2><p>When it comes to signups in WordPress, you rarely want non administrators roles to view the dashboard or admin pages just after they’ve logged in.</p><p>So, here’s an easy way to redirect non-admin users (or which ever role you&#8217;d like to select) to a default WordPress page or custom URL (of your choosing) after they log-in.</p><h3>How to use it</h3><p>There is really on four options needed for this plugin, and three of those have default values.</p><ol><li>On/Off</li><li><del\ndatetime="2014-11-04T00:53:21+00:00">Redirect minimum user role.</del> <ins\ndatetime="2014-11-04T00:53:21+00:00">Removed in 1.1.0</ins></li><li>Redirect To (A WordPress page)</li><li>Redirect URL (when Redirect to equals &#8220;A Custom URL&#8221;)</li><li>Redirect to URL by each registered role. (if empty uses URLs set above)</li></ol><p>That&#8217;s it! Once setup that user will be automatically redirected after logging in.</p><p><strong>Compatible with <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-page-template">Custom Login Page Template</a> and <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-stealth-login/" title="Custom Login Stealth Login"></a></strong></p><form\nid="edd_purchase_14333" class="edd_download_purchase_form" method="post"><div\nclass="edd_price_options"><ul><li\nid="edd_price_option_14333_2