! What is it &#8230;</p><p>The post <a\nrel="nofollow" href="https://extendd.com/plugin/multisite-featured-image/">Multisite Featured Image</a> appeared first on <a\nrel="nofollow" href="https://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p> ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Austin Passy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7332:"<h2>WordPress Multisite Network</h2><p>Do you run a WordPress multisite network? Then this plugin might be for you!</p><h3>What is it</h3><p><a\nhref="https://extendd-frostywebdesigns.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2013/11/ms-featured-image-1.png"><img\nsrc="https://extendd-frostywebdesigns.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2013/11/ms-featured-image-1-150x74.png" alt="Multisite Featured Image network settings" width="150" height="74" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-8671" /></a> This plugin does one thing, created a network settings page that allows images to be set as featured images per site in the network.</p><h3>How does it work?</h3><p>Once uploaded, this plugin <strong>will only</strong> show up in the <em>network</em> plugin admin screen located at <code>yoursite.com/<strong>wp-admin/network/plugins.php</strong></code>. If you don&#8217;t have WordPress multisite enabled, then this plugin will <strong>not</strong> work for you.</p><p>Network enabling the plugin adds the network settings page and if you&#8217;re a <em>super admin</em> you can visit the license key page to activate auto-updates in the main site of your network.</p><h3>How to use it</h3><p>Visiting the settings page will show a list of all the sites in your network with a file input field. Simply browse your media library and click <em>insert into post</em>. The full size image URL is the one we want, as its size can me modified when we output it.</p><p><strong>Included front end functions</strong></p><p>Once you&#8217;ve saved the images for each site or the sites you like you can use the following function to output the image.</p><pre>\n$site_featured_image = get_site_featured_image( $blog_id, $size = ''thumbnail'', $image = true );\n</pre><p><strong>Explanation Parameters <code>get_site_featured_image()</code></strong></p><ul><li><strong>$blog_id</strong>: current site ID. Use <code>get_current_site()->id</code> or specific integer site ID number.</li><li><strong>$size</strong>: Any WordPress media size or custom size &#8211; thumbnail, medium, large, full, etc.</li><li><strong>$image</strong>:<ul><li>true: Uutput the full image HTML (img)</li><li>false: Output image (size) URL</li></ul></li></ul><h3>Example</h3><p>Check out an example of the featured image plugin running on my <a\nhref="http://passy.co" target="_blank">Passy Network</a> blog.</p><form\nid="edd_purchase_8669" class="edd_download_purchase_form" method="post"><div\nclass="edd_price_options"><ul><li\nid="edd_price_option_8669_2-5sites" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer"><label\nfor="edd_price_option_8669_1"><input\ntype="radio"  checked=''checked'' name="edd_options[price_id][]" id="edd_price_option_8669_1" class="edd_price_option_8669" value="1"/>&nbsp;<span\nclass="edd_price_option_name" itemprop="description">2 - 5 Sites</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_sep">&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_price" itemprop="price">&#36;70.00</span></label></li><li\nid="edd_price_option_8669_singlesite" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer"><label\nfor="edd_price_option_8669_0"><input\ntype="radio"  name="edd_options[price_id][]" id="edd_price_option_8669_0" class="edd_price_option_8669" value="0"/>&nbsp;<span\nclass="edd_price_option_name" itemprop="description">Single Site</span><span\nclass="