1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"https://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-stealth-login/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"https://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-stealth-login/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 16 Apr 2013 19:49:21 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:45:"http://extendd.com/?post_type=download&p=7819";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:365:"<p>WordPress sites can be vulnerable to brute force attacks. So get the WordPress Stealth Login plugin for Custom Login and hide your wp-login.php page today!</p><p>The post <a\nrel="nofollow" href="https://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-stealth-login/">Custom Login Stealth Login</a> appeared first on <a\nrel="nofollow" href="https://extendd.com">Extendd</a>.</p> ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Austin Passy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8998:"<p><strong>This plugin requires <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login/" title="Custom Login">Custom Login</a> > version 2.x which can be downloaded for FREE in the <a\nhref="http://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login">WordPress repo</a>. <em>OR</em><em> <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/wordpress-custom-login-pro/" title="WordPress Custom Login Pro">Custom Login Pro</a>.</em></strong></p><p\nclass="note"><strong>New:</strong> In Custom Login as of version 2.2 you can now auto-install this extension from within your WordPress website! Just visit the Custom Login settings page and click &#8220;install&#8221; and enter your license key when prompted! No need to download the zip and upload the files.</p><h2>Brute force attacks</h2><p>By now you seen all the stories of WordPress sites being vulnerable to brute force attacks. What does that mean? Simple put a hacker or generated computer program is targeting <code>wp-login.php</code> pages and submitting the form hundreds if not thousands of times with the most generic username <em>admin</em> and random &#8220;popular&#8221; passwords. One step is to change your <a\nhref="http://wpdaily.co/goodbye-admin-user/">Admin</a> username, but that still leaves your site to thousands or login attempts. You can use a login IP limiter, but a hacker can use many IP&#8217;s and most likely you host will crash before all IP&#8217;s are blocked (I know because this happened to me).</p><h3>A simple solution</h3><p>How about hiding the <code>wp-login.php</code>! That is what this plugin is intended for. It gives you one solution with two options for unauthorized users.</p><ol><li><strong>Redirect</strong>: If a user doesn&#8217;t have the correct &#8220;key&#8221; and &#8220;code&#8221;, send them somewhere.</li><li><strong>Kill</strong>: If a user doesn&#8217;t have the correct &#8220;key&#8221; and &#8220;code&#8221;, kill the page with a message.</li></ol><h3>How to use it</h3><p>There is really on five options needed for this plugin, and three of those have default values.</p><ol><li>On/Off</li><li>Redirect(On)/Kill the page(Off)</li><li>Redirect URL (when Redirect is &#8220;On&#8221;)</li><li>Question (the query variable)</li><li>Answer (The query answer)</li></ol><p>That&#8217;s it! Once setup your login page can only be accessed by visiting <code>youwebsite.com/wp-login.php?question=answer</code> <strong>where</strong> <em>question</em> is the <strong>question</strong> you set as well as <em>answer</em> is the <strong>answer</strong> you set!</p><p><strong>Compatible with the new <a\nhref="http://extendd.com/plugin/custom-login-page-template">Custom Login Page Template</a>!</strong></p><form\nid="edd_purchase_7819" class="edd_download_purchase_form" method="post"><div\nclass="edd_price_options"><ul><li\nid="edd_price_option_7819_2-5sites" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer"><label\nfor="edd_price_option_7819_1"><input\ntype="radio"  checked=''checked'' name="edd_options[price_id][]" id="edd_price_option_7819_1" class="edd_price_option_7819" value="1"/>&nbsp;<span\nclass="edd_price_option_name" itemprop="description">2 - 5 Sites</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_sep">&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_price" itemprop="price">&#36;70.00</span></label></li><li\nid="edd_price_option_7819_singlesite" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer"><label\nfor="edd_price_option_7819_0"><input\ntype="radio"  name="edd_options[price_id][]" id="edd_price_option_7819_0" class="edd_price_option_7819" value="0"/>&nbsp;<span\nclass="edd_price_option_name" itemprop="description">Single Site</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_sep">&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_price" itemprop="price">&#36;25.00</span></label></li><li\nid="edd_price_option_7819_unlimited" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer"><label\nfor="edd_price_option_7819_2"><input\ntype="radio"  name="edd_options[price_id][]" id="edd_price_option_7819_2" class="edd_price_option_7819" value="2"/>&nbsp;<span\nclass="edd_price_option_name" itemprop="description">Unlimited</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_sep">&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</span><span\nclass="edd_price_option_price" itemprop="price">&#36;100.00</span></label></li></ul></div><div\nclass="edd_purchase_submit_wrapper"> <a\nhref="#" class="edd-add-to-cart but