(335, 1, '2014-10-17 15:43:16', '2014-10-17 19:43:16', '[vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="75" bottom_padding="50"][vc_column width="1/1" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][heading]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: center;">Taxi Schools</h1>\r\n[/heading][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="0" bottom_padding="45"][vc_column width="1/1" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[icon color="Accent-Color" size="large-2" image="icon-book"]</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><strong>The Eligibility of becoming a taxi driver in NSW:</strong></h4>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li>Be at least 20 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Hold a current unrestricted/unconditional drivers license (minimum C) issued in New South Wales, and have held an unrestricted drivers license issued in any Australian state or territory for at least 12 months of the previous 2 years (L, P Plate &amp; Good Behaviour licenses are not accepted)</li>\r\n	<li>Be an Australian or New Zealand Citizen, permanent resident or hold a visa allowing you to work in Australia. (Student visas OK with work restrictions)</li>\r\n	<li>Pass the AMES NMES Taxi driver communication skills English assessment</li>\r\n	<li>Pass a health check with a medical practitioner - your GP</li>\r\n	<li>Clearance from the regulator, Transport for NSW.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Roads and Maritime Services and NSW Taxi Industry require any aspiring taxi driver to complete an accredited course, the Taxicare Plus – ‘Statement of Attainment in Taxi Driver Training