(708, 10, '2014-11-11 09:01:19', '2014-11-11 14:01:19', '[vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="48" bottom_padding="15" bg_color="#ffffff"][vc_column width="1/1" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;">[icon color="Accent-Color" size="normal" image="icon-pushpin"] Tips and Tricks</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="35" bottom_padding="45" bg_color="#ffffff"][vc_column width="1/2" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We will post various tips and tricks of the trade for drivers, operators, and general users. So keep your eyes open…</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We also encourage drivers, operators, and general users of the site to send us (via email) any tips or tricks tucked in your sleeves that might help your fellow worker.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][image_with_animation image_url="707" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" img_link_target="_self"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Tips and Tricks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-11 09:01:19', '2014-11-11 14:01:19', '', 168, 'http://localhost:8080/taxideals/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(709, 10, '2014-11-11 09:03:43', '2014-11-11 14:03:43', '[vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="48" bottom_padding="15" bg_color="#ffffff"][vc_column width="1/1" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;">[icon color="Accent-Color" size="normal" image="icon-book"] Taxi Schools</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="center" top_padding="35" bottom_padding="45" bg_color="#ffffff"][vc_column width="1/2" animation="none" centered_text="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" background_color_opacity="1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>The Eligibility of becoming a taxi driver in NSW:</strong></h4>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li>Be at least 20 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Hold a current unrestricted/unconditional drivers license (minimum C) issued in New South Wales, and have held an unrestricted drivers license issued in any Australian state or territory for at least 12 months of the previous 2 years (L, P Plate &amp; Good Behaviour licenses are not accepted)</li>\r\n	<li>Be an Australian or New Zealand Citizen, permanent resident or hold a visa allowing you to work in Australia. (Student visas OK with work restrictions)</li>\r\n	<li>Pass the AMES NMES Taxi driver communication skills English assessment</li>\r\n	<li>Pass a health check with a medical practitioner - your GP</li>\r\n	<li>Clearance from the regulator, Transport for NSW.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Roads and Maritime Services and NSW Taxi Industry require any aspiring taxi driver to complete an accredited course, the Taxicare Plus – ‘Statement of Attainment in Taxi Driver Training Bronze Level’ for initial entry into the Taxi industry from a licensed training provider.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Once you have passed the tests from your training institution you will be booked to sit for a test at the Taxi authority office in Parramatta, Sydney.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Associated costs of getting a NSW taxi license:</strong></h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">These costs are given as an indication and may vary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Training Fees</strong></h5>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li>Taxicare Bronze level training Fee – $700-$900 (The training fee and quality may vary from school to school)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>External Fees</strong></h5>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li>English assessment at NSW AMES (Adult Migrant English Service)             Fee – $165</li>\r\n	<li>Medical assessment Fee – See your own Doctor                                               Fee – $50</li>\r\n	<li>4 Taxi Size Pictures (65x65mm)                                                                           Fee – $30</li>\r\n	<li>Transport NSW Min Taxi Authority processing fee (valid 6 months)             Fee – $100</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type="full_width_background" bg_position="center center" bg_repeat="no-repeat" bg_color="#ffffff" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="left" top_padding="0" bottom_padding="45"][vc_column width="1/4"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>There are a number of taxi schools or training providers in Sydney. The following are the most reputed taxi training schools and run frequent courses.</strong></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type="full_width_background